FBIS3-29803 "dreas036_c_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Feb 1994 North Korea Chongnyon Begins `Rights of Compatriots' Campaign SK2202043394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0420 GMT 22 Feb 94 SK2202043394 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, February 21 (KNS-KCNA) -- The Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) issued an appeal to all the officials of Chongnyon and Koreans in Japan on Feb. 21 in connection with the start of a "three-month campaign for the rights of compatriots." The appeal says the campaign is a mass movement of innovation to achieve a new victory in the work for national reunification and all the patriotic work of Chongnyon this year, one year before the 50th anniversary of the August 15, 1945 liberation of Korea and the 40th anniversary of the founding of Chongnyon. It calls for waging a grand movement to learn from the greatness of the sagacious leader at all Chongnyon organs, branches and families under the slogan "Let us learn from the illustrious leader Marshal Kim Chong-il!" and for strengthening the patriotic ranks of Koreans in Japan as ranks of people loyal to him. "Let us all make a tangible contribution to the reunification of Korea in the 1990s through the implementation of `10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation for the reunification of the country' in the patriotic spirit that `my destiny is linked with the destiny of the country and the nation,' actively help toward the building of socialism in the homeland and increase the ranks of our supporters and sympathizers among the Japanese people," the appeal stresses.
